    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <pb n="3r" facs="http://content.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/dms/PPN829063978/1200/0/00000007.jpg"/>
                
                <opener>
                    
                    <salute>Sir,</salute>
                    
                </opener>
                <p>In consequence of the desire you expressed to me <lb/>that I should give you a
                    few notes relative to the <lb/>Geographical <choice>
                        <sic>destribution</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">distribution</corr>
                    </choice> of mosses, I take the liberty <lb/>to hand you the <subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">f</del>
                        <add place="across">enclosed</add>
                    </subst> sketch. <choice>
                        <sic>I</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">The</corr>
                    </choice> order I follow is <lb/>the same I adopt in a <bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/v8/VWC7VAVT">Dispositio Muscorum</bibl> I lately
                    <lb/>transmitted to the <ref xml:id="a1a6e938-9a82-44fe-a6e9-389a8224fe97" corresp="#d0f89246-1549-498c-b892-461549a98cfb">
                        <orgName ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/7864271-1">Natural History Society of
                            Paris</orgName>.</ref>
                    <note xml:id="d0f89246-1549-498c-b892-461549a98cfb" corresp="#a1a6e938-9a82-44fe-a6e9-389a8224fe97">Walker-Arnott trug seine Nouvelle Disposition
                            méthodique des espèces de mousses am 18. März 1825 in der <orgName ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/7864271-1">Société d’Histoire naturelle de Paris</orgName> vor
                            (vgl. <bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/v8/VWC7VAVT">Walker-Arnott 1825</bibl>).
                            Walker-Arnott war korrespondierendes Mitglied der Gesellschaft.</note>
                    <lb/>Should much be omitted I hope you will excuse <lb/>me, as the greater part
                    is done from memory, being <lb/>very far distant from my own herbarium, and
                    there <lb/>not being any extensive one in <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2988507">Paris</placeName> so arranged that <lb/>I could at one view perceive the
                    different localities <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">of</del>
                        <add place="intralinear">
                            <lb/>for</add>
                    </subst> the same species. I have farther to beg of you to <lb/>excuse <subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">
                            <gap unit="chars" quantity="1" reason="illegible"/>
                        </del>
                        <add place="intralinear">my</add>
                    </subst> not copying it over <metamark/>
                    <add place="superlinear">again</add> for you, as my
                    time is <lb/>short in <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2988507">Paris</placeName>, and as I have
                    much yet to do.</p>
                <closer>Believe me Sir your<del rendition="#s">s</del> Sincer<subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">ely</del>
                        <add place="intralinear">e</add>
                    </subst>
                    <lb/>&amp; very Humble <choice>
                        <abbr>Serv.</abbr>
                        <expan>Servant</expan>
                    </choice>
                    <lb/>
                    <signed>G. Walker Arnott</signed>
                </closer>
                <dateline>Paris, 15 March
                    <lb/>1825}</dateline>
                <pb n="3v" facs="http://content.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/dms/PPN829063978/1200/0/00000008.jpg"/>
